Internet X.509 Public Key Infrastructure
Certificate and CRL Profile
1999", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC2459.html", target="_top", tooltip="This memo profiles the X.509 v3 certificate and X.509 v2 CRL for use in the Internet. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"];
  cites -> RFC2459;
  RFC3281 [label="RFC3281
An Internet Attribute Certificate
Profile for Authorization
2002", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC3281.html", target="_top", tooltip="This specification defines a profile for the use of X.509 Attribute Certificates in Internet Protocols.  Attribute certificates may be used in a wide range of applications and environments covering a broad spectrum of interoperability goals and a broader spectrum of operational and assurance requirements.  The goal of this document is to establish a common baseline for generic applications requiring broad interoperability as well as limited special purpose requirements.  The profile places emphasis on attribute certificate support for Internet electronic mail, IPSec, and WWW security applications. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"];
  cites -> RFC3281;
  RFC5912 [label="RFC5912
New ASN.1 Modules for the Public Key
Infrastructure Using X.509 (PKIX)
2010", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC5912.html", target="_top", tooltip="The Public Key Infrastructure using X.509 (PKIX) certificate format, and many associated formats, are expressed using ASN.1.  The current ASN.1 modules conform to the 1988 version of ASN.1.  This document updates those ASN.1 modules to conform to the 2002 version of ASN.1.  There are no bits-on-the-wire changes to any of the formats; this is simply a change to the syntax.  This document is not an Internet Standards Track specification; it is published for informational purposes."];
  cites -> RFC5912;
